<font color="#FF0000">RAELENE AND HER COMMENTS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 28 15:21:14 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I, too, am the mother of a young daughter.  I thought when I was in school that women could have it all, but, even with some wonderful opportunities, I have discovered that that is not so.  Women do seem to manage much of the household.  <br><br>
However, I do think that things are changing, even if slowly.  Men are beginning to realize that household chores come with the territory of raising a family, especially if the mother works as well.  That does not mean that they pitch in all the time, but I think they are starting to get the message.<br><br>
Time will tell...
